<title type="html"><![CDATA[IE10-pop ups- bogus updates, opinion polls]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1740&amp;p=8872#p8872"><![CDATA[
I have been using versions of Classic Shell on Windows 8 computers since May 2013. <br />I have been so frustrated and tried everything I could to over the last several months to get rid of the annoying whole,new page,pop ups- Opinion Polls (with Audio--&quot;Thank you for visiting....&quot;), Bogus Flash Player and IE update warnings that would all but lock down IE without my ending processes through Task Manager. <br />This occurred every time I would click on user login field, but before I entered my user name.  This occurred in Gmail, Hotmail, banking, box.com, DocuSign and most anything that had a login.<br /> <br />Finally, I uninstalled Classic Shell and the problem has gone away. It has removed the annoying pop ups in IE. <br /> <br />I HATE Windows 8 and loved Classic Shell as an option.  However, something had to give to get rid of the pop ups.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2280">reggietill</a> — Mon Nov 18, 2013 5:42 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
